                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 15.436,
                                "byte_start": 79981,
                                "byte_stop": 141734,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the court in 76-719,National Labor Relations Board against Local Union 103, and others will be announced by Mr. Justice White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 15.436,
                        "stop": 187.068,
                        "byte_start": 141734,
                        "byte_stop": 828337,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15071,
                            "name": "Byron R. White",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/byron_r_white",
                            "last_name": "White",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2715,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": -243367200,
                                    "date_end": 741243600,
                                    "appointing_president": "John F. Kennedy",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2715"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32699,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 55559,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/byron_r_white.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 11396,
                            "identifier": "byron_r_white"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 15.436,
                                "stop": 20.798,
                                "byte_start": 141734,
                                "byte_stop": 163259,
                                "text": "This case involves Section 8F of National Labor Relations Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.798,
                                "stop": 30.599,
                                "byte_start": 163259,
                                "byte_stop": 202443,
                                "text": "The provision which permits employers and unions in the construction industry to enter in their so called pre-hire agreements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.599,
                                "stop": 45.767,
                                "byte_start": 202443,
                                "byte_stop": 263152,
                                "text": "Setting wages and hours and working conditions, even though union does not then represent a majority of the employees that might be working on later projects, that the employer undertakes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.767,
                                "stop": 56.385,
                                "byte_start": 263152,
                                "byte_stop": 305574,
                                "text": "The section however permits the union, or the employer or the employees to seek an election at any time after the signing of pre-hire agreement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.385,
                                "stop": 67.807,
                                "byte_start": 305574,
                                "byte_stop": 351237,
                                "text": "And the union must then demonstrate its majority status, if it is to purport to represent all of the employees in the unit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.807,
                                "stop": 81.672,
                                "byte_start": 351237,
                                "byte_stop": 406721,
                                "text": "This case arises because of the National Labor Relations Board\u0027s rule, that the union\u0027s majority status is also up for challenging and fairly reflected its proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.672,
                                "stop": 88.899,
                                "byte_start": 406721,
                                "byte_stop": 435664,
                                "text": "Here the union picketed the employer claiming that the employer was in violation of his pre-hire agreement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.899,
                                "stop": 101.772,
                                "byte_start": 435664,
                                "byte_stop": 487073,
                                "text": "The employer responded by filing a charge with the board claiming that the picketing was recognitional picketing contrary to section 87."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.772,
                                "stop": 108.438,
                                "byte_start": 487073,
                                "byte_stop": 513823,
                                "text": "The board held that, that because the union had not demonstrated its majority."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.438,
                                "stop": 113.099,
                                "byte_start": 513823,
                                "byte_stop": 532422,
                                "text": "Indeed it was stipulated that it had no majority at that time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.099,
                                "stop": 131.144,
                                "byte_start": 532422,
                                "byte_stop": 604624,
                                "text": "That the union was not entitled to picket, to enforce a contract in the manner that a collective bargaining agent could do and the board went on to hold that the picketing was recognitional and in violation of 87."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.144,
                                "stop": 142.135,
                                "byte_start": 604624,
                                "byte_stop": 648614,
                                "text": "Court of Appeals reversed, the Court held essentially that although the union\u0027s standing was challengable in an election."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.135,
                                "stop": 157.963,
                                "byte_start": 648614,
                                "byte_stop": 711935,
                                "text": "It was not a challengable and unfair labor practice proceedings and the union thus here was simply picketing to enforce a contract as it was entitled to do according to the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.963,
                                "stop": 168.531,
                                "byte_start": 711935,
                                "byte_stop": 754149,
                                "text": "We reversed the judgment of the Court of Appeals for the reasons that will appear in the opinion we have filed, we agree essentially with the National Labor Relations Board."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.531,
                                "stop": 177.42,
                                "byte_start": 754149,
                                "byte_stop": 789676,
                                "text": "We think their construction, application of the act is reasonable of one even if not the only one that might be acceptable."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.42,
                                "stop": 180.374,
                                "byte_start": 789676,
                                "byte_stop": 801483,
                                "text": "So we reverse the judgment of Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.374,
                                "stop": 187.068,
                                "byte_start": 801483,
                                "byte_stop": 828337,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stewart has filed the dissenting opinion and he has joined by Justices Blackmun and Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
